<div class="post-date">Dec 23</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/1022.html" title="White white white"> White white white</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>According to the local paper we got 17 inches of snow. The temperature has not plunged yet so we walked around town and took about 80 photos with our digital camera.</p>

	<p>Here are 21 of our favorite <a href="http://homepage.mac.com/egyarnetsky/PhotoAlbum2.html">photos</a> of the morning. [<b>UPDATE</b>: <a href="http://homepage.mac.com/egyarnetsky/PhotoAlbum3.html">More photos</a>] Click on any of the photos to start the slide show. Click on any of the slide photo shots for a bigger image.</p>

	<p>Mind you, after a while you can only take so many photos of white stuff covering stuff.</p>

	<p>it is supposed to get very windy and very cold over the next couple of days. Tonight they&#8217;re calling for 3 above, a high of 11 tomorrow and -7 on Christmas eve. Wind chill of -25. ugh.  If it get&#8217;s that cold, it looking like we may well skip going to family in Ohio for Christmas.</p>

	<p>We got a call from Darlene&#8217;s sister who said her husband, a truck drive, has been stuck all night at a truck stop just north of Findlay, Ohio. Poor guy. They have blizzard advisory right now.</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

<div class="smallcat">Posted in <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?c=Madison">Madison</a></div>
<div class="smalluser"> by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a></div>
