<div class="post-date">Apr 14</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/902.html" title="Snow in mid-April???"> Snow in mid-April???</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p><img alt="snow out our window" src="http://www.ontheriversedge.com/archives/snowoutourwindow.jpg" width="300" height="203" border="1" /></p>

	<p>You have to understand that this is an area where we get dafodils and tulips in mid-March. Winter end there.</p>

	<p>But on Tuesday it snowed, covering blooming dogwoods and redbuds with heavy, slushy snow.</p>

	<p>While I was attending the Indiana Library Federation annual conference in Indianapolis, an odd front moved through that dumped 2-6 inches of really wet, heavy snow along the Ohio River valley upriver from Louisville.</p>

	<p>My boss and I were driving down I-65 when it started raining hard as we left Indy. Sometime after we passed Columbus, Ind., Charlene asked &#8220;what is that stuff.&#8221; The white stuff was only in patches, but as we drove further south it piled up.</p>

	<p>By the time we got off the Interstate onto IN-256 it was obvious we had a mid-spring snow storm. Cars and trucks were spun off the road. Soon we caught up to the snow plow that sent plumes of snow (and several trash cans) 20 feet into the air.</p>

	<p>The bushes were heavy with snow, green leaves and flowers pokes out from the snow. It was quite beautiful.</p>

	<p>I wish I had actually witnessed the event unstead of the after effects.</p>

	<p>Darlene said it started with rain and turned to a heavy sleet. Soon silver dollar-sized flakes fell in the heaviest snow seen the whole year.</p>

	<p>Darlene said her favorite, though sad episode of the snow was a police car who flew down Main Street toward a wreck on the west end of town. As he crossed the railroad bridge, he hit black ice, spun out and hit a car. That car hit another car and that car hit a house.</p>

	<p>The next morning I biked to work, the snow was already gone a mid-spring night&#8217;s dream.</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

